---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import CTAGroup from '../components/CTAGroup.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '../config/site';

const description = 'Terms of service for Technical Internship Coaching with Zeeshan Khan.';
const showEmail = !siteConfig.contactEmail.includes('PLACEHOLDER');
---

<!-- Terms should be reviewed by a qualified professional before broad commercial launch. -->

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service" description={description} path="/terms">
  <section class="section-padding">
    <div class="container-page max-w-3xl">
      <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Terms of Service', href: '/terms' }]} />

      <h1 class="text-heading">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="prose-content mt-4 text-sm text-text-muted">Last updated: June 2026</p>

      <div class="prose-content mt-10">
        <p>
          These terms describe the coaching relationship between you and me. I independently operate {siteConfig.siteName}. By enrolling or participating, you agree to these terms.
        </p>

        <h2>Independent coaching service</h2>
        <p>
          I independently operate this personal coaching service. It is not an LLC, agency, academy, institute, team, or employer-sponsored program. It is not affiliated with or endorsed by the University of Illinois Urbana-Champaign, Splunk, Cisco, or any other employer or institution mentioned.
        </p>

        <h2>Eligibility</h2>
        <p>
          The program is designed primarily for students enrolled at US colleges who are pursuing technical internships. Participation is subject to a fit assessment during the intake and strategy call process.
        </p>

        <h2>Program scope</h2>
        <p>
          The {siteConfig.programName} includes {siteConfig.sessionCount} private coaching sessions, ordinarily delivered over {siteConfig.programDurationWeeks} weeks and completed within {siteConfig.maxCompletionWeeks} calendar weeks. The program focuses on résumé positioning, application strategy, networking guidance, and interview preparation planning.
        </p>

        <h2>Price and payment</h2>
        <p>
          The founding pilot price is <strong>${siteConfig.foundingPrice} for the complete program</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>
          Payment terms are described in the coaching agreement provided before enrollment. No payment is due before services are delivered. There are no enrollment fees, setup fees, upfront fees, or maintenance fees. All payment options are interest-free with no financing charges.
        </p>
        <p>
          <em>Note: If you are an Illinois resident or if Illinois law applies to this service, additional consumer rights and payment rules may govern this relationship. Those rights are described in the coaching agreement.</em>
        </p>

        <h2>Your right to cancel</h2>
        <p>
          You may cancel your coaching agreement at any time before all services are fully performed. You will not be required to pay for services you did not receive, and you are entitled to a refund of any fees paid for services not yet provided. A cancellation form is included in the coaching agreement.
        </p>

        <h2>Included services</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>{siteConfig.sessionCount} private coaching sessions</li>
          <li>Thorough résumé review</li>
          <li>LinkedIn and application strategy</li>
          <li>Referral and networking outreach</li>
          <li>Interview preparation guidance</li>
          <li>Brief clarification support between sessions (see below)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Excluded services</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Guaranteed interviews, offers, referrals, compensation, or sponsorship</li>
          <li>Job applications completed on your behalf</li>
          <li>Mock interviews, assessment completion, or take-home assignment help</li>
          <li>Immigration, legal, tax, or financial advice</li>
          <li>Indefinite support until an internship is obtained</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Student responsibilities</h2>
        <p>You agree to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Commit approximately two to three hours per week</li>
          <li>Attend scheduled sessions and complete agreed assignments</li>
          <li>Provide accurate information and truthful résumé content</li>
          <li>Verify every metric and claim on your résumé before submitting applications</li>
          <li>Maintain an application tracker and apply consistently when materials are ready</li>
          <li>Communicate promptly when blocked or unable to attend</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Truthful information</h2>
        <p>
          All résumé claims must be truthful and defensible. Fabricated experience, projects, metrics, or skills are not permitted. I do not apply for roles or complete assessments for clients.
        </p>

        <h2>Scheduling and missed sessions</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>At least 12 hours&apos; notice is requested for ordinary rescheduling.</li>
          <li>One courtesy late-rescheduling exception is available per engagement.</li>
          <li>Reasonable flexibility is offered for genuine emergencies.</li>
          <li>A session missed without notice from you ordinarily counts as an included session.</li>
          <li>If I cancel a session, it is rescheduled and does not count against you.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Between-session support</h2>
        <p>
          Brief clarification questions may be sent between sessions, generally consolidated into one message thread per week. Responses are normally provided within two business days. Extensive editing, new résumé-review rounds, urgent interview coaching, and major strategy work occur during scheduled sessions unless separately agreed in writing.
        </p>

        <h2>Cancellation and refunds</h2>
        <p>
          The complete refund and cancellation terms are described in the coaching agreement you receive before enrollment. The following principles apply:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>You may cancel at any time before full delivery.</li>
          <li>You are not required to pay for services not received.</li>
          <li>Fees paid for services already provided are not automatically refunded.</li>
          <li>If an included service cannot be delivered, you will receive an equivalent replacement or a proportional refund.</li>
          <li>Any refund due on cancellation is issued within five business days of your cancellation notice, along with a statement of fees received and fees refunded.</li>
          <li>There are no interest charges or late-payment penalties.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>No guaranteed outcomes</h2>
        <p>
          Coaching does not guarantee interviews, offers, referrals, compensation, or sponsorship. Results depend on your effort, skills, preparation, eligibility, execution, application timing, employer decisions, and market conditions — none of which are within my control.
        </p>

        <h2>Not professional advice</h2>
        <p>
          Coaching is not immigration advice, legal advice, tax advice, or financial advice. Consult qualified professionals for those matters.
        </p>

        <h2>AI consent and opt-out</h2>
        <p>
          With your explicit consent, a third-party AI tool may assist with reviewing your materials, with identifying information removed where reasonably possible. You may opt out of AI-assisted processing at any time without affecting your access to coaching or your price. Your preference is honored for the duration of the engagement.
        </p>

        <h2>Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          See the <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for details on data collection, retention, deletion, and third-party processors.
        </p>

        <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
        <p>
          Coaching frameworks, rubrics, templates, worksheets, and written action points provided as part of the program are for your personal career use. You may not redistribute these materials commercially or present them as your own published work.
        </p>
        <p>
          Your résumé, project descriptions, personal stories, and other materials you create remain yours. The restriction above applies to my proprietary coaching materials, not to your own documents.
        </p>

        <h2>Right to end engagement</h2>
        <p>
          I may end an engagement if you provide dishonest information, are abusive or disrespectful, repeatedly fail to participate without explanation, or request prohibited services such as having me apply for roles or complete assessments on your behalf. In such cases, a fair refund for genuinely undelivered work will be provided where appropriate.
        </p>

        <h2>Consumer notice</h2>
        <p>
          General educational planning services may be available free of charge from the Illinois Student Assistance Commission (<a href="https://isac.org">isac.org</a>) and may also be offered by other public or not-for-profit entities, such as a public library or an institution of higher learning.
        </p>
        <p>
          <em>If you are an Illinois resident or if Illinois law applies to this engagement, additional consumer rights and disclosures are provided in the coaching agreement before you sign.</em>
        </p>

        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>
          These terms may be updated as the service evolves. Material changes will be reflected on this page with an updated date. Terms in effect at the time of your enrollment govern your engagement.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For questions about these terms or the coaching relationship,
          {showEmail ? (
            <> contact <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.contactEmail}`}>{siteConfig.contactEmail}</a>.</>
          ) : (
            <> use the contact method provided on this website.</>
          )}
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12">
        <CTAGroup primary={{ label: 'View Program', href: '/program' }} />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
